Description: Polaric Server: AIS data plugin. 
 The "Polaric Server" is mainly a web based service to present tracking 
 information (mainly APRS) on maps and where the information is updated at real-
 time. It is originally targeted for use by radio amateurs in voluntary search
 and rescue service in Norway. It consists of a web application and a server 
 program (APRS daemon). It can function as an offline service if required. 
 .
 This is a plugin that can read AIS data from a TCP stream or a serial interface
 and present AIS vessels as moving points on the map. It is used on aprs.no with 
 data from the Norwegian Maritime Authority.
